@areadenial2343 Sorry for the really long answer. Lets focus on the horizontal movement. Basically, as you rotate the assembly clockwise, more power is given to the horizontal stroke, until at 90 degrees, 100% of the movement is transmitted to the horizontal stroke, and there is zero power given to the vertical stroke.
The stroke length is the amplitude of the output, but the frequency is the same.
So as you increase the clockwise rotation, the amplitude of the output power increases in X and reduces in Y, or vice versa.

